{
  "abstract": "Groundnut (Arachis hypogaea 1.) is the 6th most important oilseed crop and the 13 th\r\nmost important food crop in the world. It is grown in an area of 26.4 million ha with a total\r\nproduction of 37.1 million metric tones and an average productivity of 1.4 metric tones ha-'.\r\nDeveloping countries account for 96%of the global area and 92% of the global production of\r\nthe crop. Groundnut is grown under both high input and subsistence farming conditions. High\r\nyields are realized under high input irrigated condition, where diseases and pets are controlled.\r\nYields in excess of 4 t ha-' are not uncommon under such conditions.............",
